In article <9402060818592.davesparks.DLITE@delphi.com>,
Dave Sparks <davesparks@delphi.com> wrote:
>Does anybody know how secure the password protection is on the backup
>software that comes bundled with Colorado tape drives?  It doesn't seem to
>have any export restrictions, so that's probably a clue, but I'm wondering
>if anyone has any further knowledge on the subject.

I did a security review of their program a while back, and found
that the password is stored in the clear on the tape.  Recovering
the original password is trivial.  The actual data on the
tape is not encrypted.

-- Paul Kocher
